//Tendons - Tractus iliotibialis

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 - Soft parts of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Tendons - Tractus iliotibialis' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Tear' checkbox is enabled
And 'Enthesiopathy („runners knee“)' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tear' checkbox
Then 'Intramuscular' radio button is enabled
And 'Intratendinous' radio button is enabled
And 'Insertion' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone bruise' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retraction' radio button
Then 'Dimension' input field is enabled

When I select 'Enthesiopathy („runners knee“)' checkbox
Then 'Thickening/Edema between Tractus & Femur' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bursitis of the iliotibial band' checkbox is enabled
And 'Muscular atrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fibrovascular tissue between iliotibial band and femur' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ganglion cyst' checkbox is enabled